 the Erd\\H{o}s-Falconer distance\nconjecture holds in odd-dimensional spaces when we study distances between two\nsets: one set lies on a variety (paraboloids or spheres), and the other set is\narbitrary in $\\mathbb{F}_q^d$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 23 Sep 2018 23:57:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Sep 2018 16:53:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 25 Oct 2018 17:22:51 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 7 Nov 2018 23:42:54 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 15 Apr 2019 01:02:57 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2019 22:13:11 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 13:16:13 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 26 Nov 2019 12:34:16 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Sun, 15 Mar 2020 15:50:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-17"}
